<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
We did not find any original material for this name either in MAF (MAF-Pourret collection), and P (the general collection and the special 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Pourret’s">Pourret's</normalizedToken>
collection named &quot; 
<taxonomicName class="Aves" family="Fringillidae" genus="Chloris" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Chloris narbonensis" order="Passeriformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="narbonensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Chloris narbonensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
&quot;), where Pierre 
<normalizedToken originalValue="André">Andre</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken originalValue="Pourret’s">Pourret's</normalizedToken>
(1754-1818) collections are mainly kept (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.48631" author="Stafleu, FA" journalOrPublisher="Zpravy Ceskoslovenske Botanicke Spolecnosti pri Ceskoslovenske Akademii Ved" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B25" refString="Stafleu, FA, Cowan, RS, 1983. Taxonomic literature, ed. 2, vol. 4. Utrecht, Bohn, Scheltema &amp; Holkema. https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.48631" title="Taxonomic literature, ed. 2, vol. 4. Utrecht, Bohn, Scheltema &amp; Holkema." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.48631" year="1983">Stafleu and Cowan 1983</bibRefCitation>
), or in other relevant herbaria (BM, FI, MPU, and UPS; see 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.48631" author="Stafleu, FA" journalOrPublisher="Zpravy Ceskoslovenske Botanicke Spolecnosti pri Ceskoslovenske Akademii Ved" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B25" refString="Stafleu, FA, Cowan, RS, 1983. Taxonomic literature, ed. 2, vol. 4. Utrecht, Bohn, Scheltema &amp; Holkema. https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.48631" title="Taxonomic literature, ed. 2, vol. 4. Utrecht, Bohn, Scheltema &amp; Holkema." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.48631" year="1983">Stafleu and Cowan 1983</bibRefCitation>
: 368). It seems, therefore, that the original material for this name is lost. This possibility is not surprising giving 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Pourret’s">Pourret's</normalizedToken>
dramatic escape from France to Spain in 1789 and his forced exile (
<bibRefCitation author="Galibert, L" journalOrPublisher="Italian Botanist" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B11" refString="Galibert, L, 1856. Biographie de Pierre-Andre Pourret. Narbonne, Imprimerie D'Emmanuel Caillard." title="Biographie de Pierre-Andre Pourret. Narbonne, Imprimerie D'Emmanuel Caillard." year="1856">Galibert 1856</bibRefCitation>
), followed by several war events (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.48631" author="Stafleu, FA" journalOrPublisher="Zpravy Ceskoslovenske Botanicke Spolecnosti pri Ceskoslovenske Akademii Ved" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B25" refString="Stafleu, FA, Cowan, RS, 1983. Taxonomic literature, ed. 2, vol. 4. Utrecht, Bohn, Scheltema &amp; Holkema. https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.48631" title="Taxonomic literature, ed. 2, vol. 4. Utrecht, Bohn, Scheltema &amp; Holkema." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.48631" year="1983">Stafleu and Cowan 1983</bibRefCitation>
: 368). Because the original material of 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. villosus" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="villosus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">C. villosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is lost, we have decided to choose a neotype represented by the specimen G00007761 housed at G-DC. This specimen has been previously selected by Cristofolini and Fumeaux (Cristofolini and Troia 2006) as the lectotype of 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. triflorus" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="triflorus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">C. triflorus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken originalValue="L’Hér">L'Her</normalizedToken>
. [1791]; an illegitimate name (a later homonym of 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. triflorus" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="triflorus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">C. triflorus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Lam. [1786]) being conspecific with 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. villosus" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="villosus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">C. villosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Pourr. (see 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/1219931" author="Polhill, RM" journalOrPublisher="Phytotaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B18" refString="Polhill, RM, 1978. Proposal to conserve and retypify the name Cytisus (Leguminosae). Taxon 27(5/6): 556-559. https://doi.org/10.2307/1219931" title="Proposal to conserve and retypify the name Cytisus (Leguminosae). Taxon 27 (5 / 6): 556 - 559." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/1219931" year="1978">Polhill 1978</bibRefCitation>
; Cristofolini and Troia 2006). Importantly, as 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Cytisus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cytisus triflorus" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="triflorus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Cytisus triflorus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken originalValue="L’Hér">L'Her</normalizedToken>
. has been accepted as the conserved type for the generic name 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Cytisus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cytisus" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Cytisus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Desf., nom. cons. (Appendix III of the ICN), it becomes automatically a homotypic synonym of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Cytisus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cytisus villosus" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="villosus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Cytisus villosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Pourr. - which is the accepted name of the generitype of this genus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
